`contMDiffWithinAt (I.prod I') (I'.prod I) (↑(n * 1)) (fun x => f (x.1)) (prod.fst ⁻¹' range (I.prod I')) (x₀, (tangentMap I I' f) x₀)`

This goal is a `contMDiffWithinAt` statement. We have `hf : ContMDiffAt I I' n f x₀.proj`.
The definition of `contMDiffWithinAt` involves `contMDiffAt` and `eventuallyEq`.
The `simp` tactic should be able to use `hf` to prove this.

```tactics
  simp [hf, tangentMap]
```
The complete code is now:
```tactics
